  "prompt": "How can I become member of Mensa India?",
  "response": "To become a member of Mensa India, you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Take an IQ Test\n- You must score at 98th percentile or above on a standardized, approved intelligence test\n- This means scoring in the top 2% of the general population\n\n2. Qualifying Tests\n- Mensa India accepts scores from various standard IQ tests\n- Some accepted tests include:\n  - Ravens Progressive Matrices\n  - Stanford-Binet\n  - Cattell Culture Fair Test\n  - Wechsler Adult Intelligence Scale (WAIS)\n\n3. Application Process\n- If you have a qualifying test score, you can apply online\n- Visit the official Mensa India website\n- Fill out the membership application form\n- Submit your qualifying test score documentation\n\n4. Alternative Testing\n- If you don't have a prior qualifying test score, Mensa India conducts its own admission tests\n- These tests are periodically conducted in major cities\n- Check their website for test dates and locations\n\n5. Membership Fees\n- Pay the required membership fees\n- Fees vary and can be checked on their official website\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Visit www.mensaindia.org\n- Contact them directly for the most current membership requirements\n- Attend local Mensa events to learn more about the organization",
